31.1.0 Specific objectives
By the end of this topic, the
leamer should be able to:
a) describe converging lenses
and diverging lenses
b) describe using ray
diagrams the principal
focus, the optical centre
and the focal length of a
thin lens
c) determine experimentally
the focal length of a
converging lens
d) locate images formed by
thin lenses using ray
construction method
e) describe the characteristics
of images formed by thin
lenses
f) explain image formation in
the human eye
describe the defects of
vision in the human eye
and how they can be
corrected
h) describe the use of lenses
in various optical devices
i) solve numerical problems
involving the lens formula

fonnula
